# Executive verdict

[COMPUTED] The preferred singleton-support definition from exploration 001 is already killed at the static support/triad-geometry level. No exact five-role support of single helical modes, even with full conjugate-sign freedom, can realize Tao's three core early channels

```text
a1^2 -> a2,
a1^2 -> a3,
a2 a3 -> a3.
```

[CHECKED] The obstruction is geometric, not helicity-specific. Helicity signs only modify the coefficients once a triad exists. They do not change the triad-closure equation

```text
εj kj + εm km + εn kn = 0,   ε• ∈ {±1},
```

which is the only fact needed here.

[CHECKED] Therefore the Phase 0 preferred object should not proceed to Phase 2. Only the packetized backup definition survives this exploration.

# Chosen minimal support and rationale

[CHECKED] I audited the most favorable version of the preferred object:

- one representative wavevector `k_j` per Tao role,
- one helical sign `σ_j` per role,
- full access to the conjugate mirrors `-k_j`,
- no extra packet structure.

This is the smallest exact support that could possibly make the preferred definition sharp. If this object already fails, the failure is a genuine obstruction for the singleton-mode version, not a failure of bookkeeping.

## Role-to-triad constraints

For any desired monomial `am an -> aj`, exact Fourier/helical NS requires a triad with some sign choices

```text
εj kj + εm km + εn kn = 0,
```

because the equation for a target mode at `±kj` is built from source modes at `±km` and `±kn`.

Applying this to the desired Tao channels gives:

1. `a1^2 -> a2`

```text
ε2 k2 + (β2 + γ2) k1 = 0.
```

Since `β2, γ2 ∈ {±1}`, the coefficient `β2 + γ2` is either `±2` or `0`. The `0` case would force `k2 = 0`, impossible. Hence

```text
k2 = ± 2 k1.
```

2. `a1^2 -> a3`

By the same argument,

```text
k3 = ± 2 k1.
```

So the pump and seed channels force roles 2 and 3 onto the same conjugate wavevector pair.

3. `a2 a3 -> a3`

This requires

```text
α k3 + β k2 + γ k3 = 0,
α,β,γ ∈ {±1}.
```

But once `k2 = ± 2k1` and `k3 = ± 2k1`, this becomes

```text
(α c3 + β c2 + γ c3) k1 = 0,
c2,c3 ∈ {+2,-2}.
```

The accompanying brute-force sign check in
`code/sign_constraints.py`
shows there is no choice of `c2, c3, α, β, γ` that makes this vanish.

# Exact helical interaction equations

[VERIFIED] In the helical basis,

```text
(∂t + ν|k|^2) u_{s_k}(k)
  = -1/4 ∑_{k+p+q=0} ∑_{s_p,s_q}
      (s_p |p| - s_q |q|)
      (h_{s_p}(p) × h_{s_q}(q) · h_{s_k}(k))̄
      u_{s_p}(p) u_{s_q}(q).
```

[CHECKED] For the singleton-support audit, the only issue is whether the desired monomials can exist at all. Since the triad-closure constraints fail before coefficients are even compared, the coefficient forms can be recorded only structurally:

- if `a1^2 -> a2` exists, its coefficient is
  `C(k2; ±k1, ±k1; σ2, σ1, σ1)`;
- if `a1^2 -> a3` exists, its coefficient is
  `C(k3; ±k1, ±k1; σ3, σ1, σ1)`;
- if `a2 a3 -> a3` existed, its coefficient would be
  `C(k3; ±k2, ±k3; σ3, σ2, σ3)`.

But the third channel never exists once the first two are imposed.

